in the lines, take flight

02:33.280 --> 02:35.145
Dreams never die

02:40.630 --> 02:44.669
Keep the colors
in the lines

02:44.720 --> 02:47.462
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight.

02:51.040 --> 02:54.168
[ phone clicking ]

02:55.390 --> 02:58.211
[ line ringing ]

02:58.260 --> 02:59.739
- Charley: Hello?
- Hey, Charley?

02:59.780 --> 03:01.645
Hey, Darla.

03:04.050 --> 03:06.359
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm, um...
[ sniffles ]

03:06.400 --> 03:07.697
I'm fine.
I'm--

03:07.750 --> 03:10.184
I'm just not
feeling well today.

03:11.270 --> 03:14.489
Last night was a lot.

03:14.540 --> 03:16.223
Believe me, I, uh--

03:16.280 --> 03:19.579
I know how stressful it is
when parents VISIt.

03:21.200 --> 03:23.452
I admire the courage
you showed.

03:25.900 --> 03:30.724
Um, I was wondering that,

03:30.770 --> 03:34.240
if it's not too busy today,
ifI could stay home.

03:34.300 --> 03:35.813
Yeah, of course.

03:35.860 --> 03:37.111
Of course.
Get some rest.

03:37.170 --> 03:40.685
Things are--
things are running smoothly.

03:40.740 --> 03:42.992
Darla,
I have to go.

03:43.040 --> 03:44.519
Feel better, okay?

03:47.790 --> 03:50.782
Apologies for dropping in
on you like this, Charley.

03:50.830 --> 03:53.390
Luther, Rainey,
please, have a seat.

03:53.450 --> 03:56.089
We'll stand
if it's all the same.

03:56.140 --> 03:58.313
Luther: We're gonna
cut to the chase
out of respect.

03:58.360 --> 04:00.965
If we mill with you,

04:01.020 --> 04:03.329
the Landrys are threatening
to pull our leases.

04:03.370 --> 04:05.361
Take your land?

04:05.410 --> 04:08.152
Well, they can't
just do that.

04:09.510 --> 04:11.239
[ sighs ]

04:13.250 --> 04:14.945
No.

04:14.990 --> 04:17.208
No, no, it's not right.

04:17.250 --> 04:19.241
You have to fight this.

04:19.300 --> 04:21.165
I will help you
fight this.

04:21.210 --> 04:23.030
We can go to the press,
get the story out--

04:23.080 --> 04:25.389
We just don't think
this is a fight

04:25.430 --> 04:27.125
we can afford having

04:27.170 --> 04:30.697
or one you can
help us win.

04:30.740 --> 04:31.877
I'm sorry.

04:36.360 --> 04:39.875
[ chattering, laughing ]

04:57.420 --> 05:01.766
"For his valiant efforts
to protect the South."

05:17.830 --> 05:21.869
Hi, may I speak
to Martin Bennington, please?

05:23.580 --> 05:25.662
Sure, this is
Charley Bordelon-W--

05:27.670 --> 05:29.319
This is Charley Bordelon.

05:30.980 --> 05:33.016
Yes, thank you.

05:38.940 --> 05:40.020
Where you been, Rid?

05:40.070 --> 05:41.981
- Nova.
- [ chuckles ]

05:42.030 --> 05:43.634
Been too long,
brother.

05:43.690 --> 05:46.295
[ laughing ]

05:46.340 --> 05:49.070
Shoot,
I haven't been nowhere
but out here in the 9th.

05:49.130 --> 05:50.518
Trying to get my paper.

05:50.560 --> 05:52.608
- Ain't a damn thing
changed.
- Right.

05:52.650 --> 05:56.529
But you?
I've been seeing you
all over my TV.

05:56.570 --> 05:58.083
What's up next
for you, Big Time?

05:58.140 --> 06:00.176
Please,
it's not even
like that.

06:00.220 --> 06:01.653
[ both laugh ]

06:01.700 --> 06:04.225
All right,
so you have me
over here.

06:04.270 --> 06:05.134
What you pawning?

06:07.880 --> 06:11.577
Damn. Pearls?

06:11.630 --> 06:14.793
This legit, Nova.
Where'd you get this from?

06:14.850 --> 06:16.579
It was a gift.

06:16.630 --> 06:19.064
So, you want me to take it
to my man's and let him know

06:19.110 --> 06:21.021
that you gonna come back
and pick it up?

06:21.070 --> 06:22.719
'Cause he'll probably hold it
for about a week for you.

06:22.770 --> 06:25.238
Nah, just,
uh-- just sell it
straight up, Rid.

06:25.290 --> 06:27.850
It's-- it's time
to move on.

06:27.900 --> 06:29.424
Gotta move on.

06:29.470 --> 06:32.166
Just meet me with the money
at Trevor's rent party.

06:32.210 --> 06:34.519
I know the brother's
gotta be going through it
since he got out of OPP.

06:34.560 --> 06:36.425
Yeah, bet.

06:36.480 --> 06:39.040
Heads'll be happy
to see you, too, Nova.

06:39.090 --> 06:40.569
It'll feel good
to be seen.

06:40.610 --> 06:42.828
- [ chuckles ]
- Hey.

06:45.010 --> 06:47.831
- All right.
- All right.

06:47.880 --> 06:49.529
Fantastic.

06:49.580 --> 06:51.059
[ knocking ]

06:51.100 --> 06:53.352
Okay, I will
see you shortly.

06:57.320 --> 06:58.457
Morning, sir.

06:58.500 --> 06:59.842
Good morning, ma'am.

06:59.890 --> 07:03.769
I had a good time
talking last night.

07:05.200 --> 07:06.599
And this morning.

07:08.510 --> 07:11.980
Well, the evening
ended differently
than I thought it would.

07:14.860 --> 07:16.771
But I had
a good time, too.

07:16.820 --> 07:19.129
I realized that
we need to talk more,

07:19.170 --> 07:21.866
get into...

07:21.910 --> 07:23.866
this more.

07:23.920 --> 07:26.878
Too grown for games
and uncertainty.

07:26.920 --> 07:29.525
Come on, now.
Way too grown.

07:29.570 --> 07:31.265
[ chuckles ]

07:31.320 --> 07:32.969
More to come_
when the time IS rIght.

07:34.800 --> 07:36.017
When the time is right.

07:38.150 --> 07:39.492
Rainey and Luther
come to see you?

07:42.760 --> 07:45.320
[ scoffing ]
These damn Landrys.

07:45.370 --> 07:46.928
They're not
gonna stop, Charley.

07:46.980 --> 07:51.462
Yeah, you're right,
they're not gonna stop.

07:51.510 --> 07:53.728
Until I stop them.

07:59.470 --> 08:03.167
I just got off the phone
with Martin Bennington.

08:06.260 --> 08:09.479
Are you trying to poach
a Landry for a Landry?

08:15.710 --> 08:19.055
Can you handle
Ralph Angel's Brix test
over at the farm today?

08:22.930 --> 08:24.272
Yeah, I got it.

08:32.510 --> 08:34.284
I hope you know
what you're doing.

08:36.290 --> 08:37.598
I do.

09:03.840 --> 09:06.308
Hey, pretty lady.
[ chuckles ]

09:07.500 --> 09:09.889
Hollywood,

09:09.940 --> 09:13.023
you better learn
how to make a phone call
sometime.

09:13.070 --> 09:16.244
Surprising folks,
you're gonna get a surprise
for yourself one time.

09:16.290 --> 09:18.599
Yeah, well,
I like your surprises.

09:18.640 --> 09:21.029
Come over here.
Mmm.

09:21.080 --> 09:23.332
What you got there?

09:23.380 --> 09:26.383
Vitamins,
iron supplements,
nothing special.

09:26.430 --> 09:28.819
I thought you weren't
coming back until tomorrow.

09:28.870 --> 09:30.565
What kind of greeting
is that, huh?

09:30.610 --> 09:33.215
"Why you back so early?"
You're a cold piece, Vi.

09:33.260 --> 09:36.218
[ chuckles ]
Oh, I didn't say all that.

09:36.270 --> 09:38.306
Ijust...

09:38.360 --> 09:41.261
I don't know,
thought the deposition
would take a while longer.

09:41.310 --> 09:44.393
They just wanted to know
about safety procedures
on the rig that day.

09:44.450 --> 09:47.408
The lawyers think the company
been cutting corners.

09:47.450 --> 09:49.054
Really?

09:49.110 --> 09:52.716
But I think
we about to go up
a little bit higher.

09:54.330 --> 09:56.457
See, we gonna take
your dreams

09:56.500 --> 09:58.968
and make them
bigger and better.

09:59.030 --> 10:02.500
- Bigger and better?
- Mm-hmm.

10:02.550 --> 10:04.632
I'm gonna spoil you

10:04.690 --> 10:06.499
till you can't
take no more.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.513
Now, I know you want
some sandwich,

10:11.560 --> 10:13.118
so go ahead
and eat that.

10:25.660 --> 10:28.356
Louisiana iris.

10:31.450 --> 10:34.101
- Mother_Brown!
- Continue.

10:38.720 --> 10:40.585
Pleasure to see you.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.449
Pleasure's all mine.

10:44.810 --> 10:47.244
Time is short,
so I'll get straight to it.

10:47.290 --> 10:51.852
My people at the statehouse
and in Congress have come
bearing good news.

10:53.430 --> 10:58.641
The 9th Ward is getting
a block grant from HHS.

10:58.700 --> 11:01.168
That's amazing!

11:01.220 --> 11:03.688
Thank goodness!

11:03.750 --> 11:05.479
Thankyou.

11:05.530 --> 11:07.521
See, fresh thinking
is what we need

11:07.570 --> 11:10.448
to be sure we make
the best of this.

11:10.490 --> 11:12.799
I want to see you
on the task force

11:12.840 --> 11:14.626
that'll decide
how it's spent.

11:14.670 --> 11:17.491
Oh, no,
I'm-- I'm flattered,

11:17.540 --> 11:19.883
but if you're there, I--

11:19.940 --> 11:21.669
I know things
will be fine.

11:22.980 --> 11:24.891
_ Boardrooms
just aren't my style.

11:24.940 --> 11:27.989
But it ain't
about your style.

11:28.030 --> 11:30.419
It's about doing
what needs to be done

11:30.470 --> 11:32.893
when it needs
to be done.

11:36.210 --> 11:38.815
Well,
just think about it.

11:38.870 --> 11:41.509
You've done all the work.

11:41.570 --> 11:44.255
You might as well
see it through to the end.

11:58.320 --> 12:01.790
This, dude-- have you
seen this before?

12:01.850 --> 12:05.934
[ sighs ]
Yeah, of course.

12:07.330 --> 12:11.198
Okay, and you understand
what it is?

12:11.250 --> 12:15.027
Yeah, man, I--
I know what it is.

12:15.080 --> 12:19.779
[ scoffs ]
I mean, dude, you're always
talking about how woke you are.

12:19.820 --> 12:22.516
Why are you acting like
this isn't a big deal?

12:22.560 --> 12:24.551
Look, I know
you're from out West.

12:24.610 --> 12:27.511
But in the South,
these kind of things
are everywhere.

12:27.570 --> 12:29.788
I mean, it's just
part of history.

12:31.620 --> 12:34.703
Well, maybe
you see history.

12:34.750 --> 12:35.648
All I see his hate.

12:36.880 --> 12:38.268
Christian:
Okay, well...

12:38.320 --> 12:40.094
what's the alternative?

12:42.890 --> 12:44.403
I mean, my--
my take on it is

12:44.450 --> 12:48.272
if we pretend
that the Confederacy
never existed,

12:48.330 --> 12:51.709
then we forget
how far we've come.

12:59.300 --> 13:02.554
[ both laughing ]

13:06.000 --> 13:07.729
I'm glad you called,
Charley.

13:07.780 --> 13:09.168
Your offer's appealing.

13:10.870 --> 13:12.428
And you are, too.

13:14.610 --> 13:16.828
Would you like
a sparkling water?

13:16.880 --> 13:18.575
I'll take a single malt.

13:20.190 --> 13:22.055
- Before noon?
- LIve a lIttle.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.317
[ both chuckle ]

13:23.360 --> 13:25.828
Well, some of us
can't afford

13:25.890 --> 13:27.664
to mix
work and play.

13:28.930 --> 13:31.535
That's not
a prIVIlege I get.

13:31.590 --> 13:33.933
- I admire your
discipline, Charley.
-Hmm.

13:33.980 --> 13:37.063
- [ liquid pouring ]
- You're self-made.

13:37.120 --> 13:40.499
I wish we were, too,
my family.

13:40.550 --> 13:42.245
It would make us
better people.

13:42.290 --> 13:45.771
Sam and Jacob do seem
untouched by human empathy.

13:45.820 --> 13:47.208
Well, that's not me.

13:47.260 --> 13:49.069
Sure, I got
a boost in life,

13:49.130 --> 13:51.997
but not carrying
the Landry/Boudreaux name

13:52.040 --> 13:53.917
helps me sleep
a little better at night.

13:55.920 --> 14:01.040
I think we both
understand family.

14:01.100 --> 14:05.355
And their histories
can be...

14:06.930 --> 14:08.659
messy,

14:08.710 --> 14:10.405
complicated.

14:13.280 --> 14:14.884
But you can't
escape it.

14:14.940 --> 14:17.807
Blood is blood.

14:19.550 --> 14:21.677
But business is business.

14:23.290 --> 14:27.420
_It seems we both believe
In progress above all else,

14:27.470 --> 14:31.167
which is what
the Queen Sugar Mill
is all about.

14:34.170 --> 14:37.389
So, please...

14:37.440 --> 14:39.863
may I show you
what we have to offer you?

14:39.920 --> 14:42.002
Lead the way.

14:45.920 --> 14:48.354
- [ line ringing ]
- [ muttering ]
Pick up the phone.

14:49.620 --> 14:51.224
[ sniffles ]

14:52.800 --> 14:56.054
[ phone ringing ]

14:58.850 --> 15:02.968
[ ringing continues ]

15:05.900 --> 15:07.242
[ line clicks ]

15:16.350 --> 15:19.080
I know you're upset.

15:19.130 --> 15:20.950
Maybe we could, um--

15:21.000 --> 15:22.786
maybe if we just
could talk about it

15:22.830 --> 15:24.559
a little bit.

15:25.700 --> 15:28.430
[ sighs ]

15:30.010 --> 15:31.875
Please, Ralph Angel.

15:31.930 --> 15:34.148
Tell me anything.
Tell me something.

15:34.190 --> 15:37.921
Ralph Angel, just...

15:37.980 --> 15:40.790
yell at me,
scream at me.

15:40.850 --> 15:44.934
Call me names,
anything!

15:44.980 --> 15:48.108
Get angry at me,
anything!

15:48.160 --> 15:49.934
[ sighs ]

15:52.560 --> 15:56.291
- Keep your hands
on the wheel...
- Ralph Angel, please.

15:59.040 --> 16:03.477
- Keep your eyes
on the prize...
- Please come home.

16:05.610 --> 16:07.999
- Time will change
the way you feel...
- What home?

16:08.050 --> 16:10.041
[ sobbing ]

16:16.230 --> 16:18.278
[ Darla sobbing ]

16:18.320 --> 16:21.926
Keep your doubt
for the truth

16:25.280 --> 16:29.899
And your blinds
open wide

16:31.770 --> 16:34.728
'Cause every crater
on the moon

16:36.340 --> 16:40.640
Still emits a shine...

16:50.220 --> 16:52.131
[ children playing
in distance ]

17:02.100 --> 17:04.318
- Woman: There she is.
- Blue: Mom!

17:04.370 --> 17:06.361
Okay, bye.

17:06.410 --> 17:08.059
Darla: Hey.

17:08.110 --> 17:11.068
Hi, baby.
How was school?

17:11.110 --> 17:13.670
- Fun.
- Good.
I missed you.

17:13.720 --> 17:16.678
I thought Pop
was picking me up.

17:16.730 --> 17:19.290
He was,
but something came up.

17:19.340 --> 17:20.819
- Wanna play "I Spy"?
- Yeah!

17:20.860 --> 17:24.330
Okay.
Get in the car.

17:24.390 --> 17:26.642
You want to get
some ice cream afterwards?

17:26.690 --> 17:29.511
- Yes, but only the winner
gets ice cream.
- Mmm, okay.

17:33.700 --> 17:36.999
- And I will win it!
-Mmm.

17:37.050 --> 17:39.610
- [ chatter ]
- So fresh, yes,
I'm so blessed

17:39.660 --> 17:42.925
Minor-League thinking
in the way of progress

17:42.970 --> 17:46.098
No stress,
Matthew McConaughey me,
driving in that Lincoln...

17:46.150 --> 17:47.708
- Rid: Yo, Nova.
- Hi.

17:47.760 --> 17:49.887
Nova:
Hey, hey.

17:49.930 --> 17:51.841
This here is Mia.

17:51.890 --> 17:53.198
- Hi.
- HI.

17:53.240 --> 17:55.674
- Jasmine, Darius.
- Hi.

17:55.720 --> 17:56.971
- Nice to meet you.
- Jasmine: How you doing?

17:57.030 --> 17:58.509
I volunteered
at your ZIka clean-up.

17:58.550 --> 18:00.279
Thank you
for coming out.

18:00.340 --> 18:02.763
Thank you for everything
you've been doing in
the community.

18:02.820 --> 18:06.290
- Okay.
- No cameras with you.

18:06.340 --> 18:07.557
We the only audience
you peddling

18:07.600 --> 18:08.771
alternative facts to
today?

18:10.520 --> 18:11.680
I'm not peddling
anything.

18:11.740 --> 18:13.128
Oh, so you
actually believe

18:13.170 --> 18:14.956
that the Lower 9th
was at risk for Zika?

18:15.000 --> 18:17.218
I simply laid out the facts
of what could have happened.

18:17.270 --> 18:19.431
And apologized for the fear
that that created.

18:19.480 --> 18:20.651
You apologized how?

18:20.700 --> 18:22.782
With that sham _
of a community meeting?

18:22.840 --> 18:24.831
- Jasmine: Mia, come on.
- I think you need to
back up off me.

18:24.880 --> 18:28.441
Nova, mothers took off work
so that you and the doctors
could examine them

18:28.490 --> 18:32.017
and tell them
what you already knew--
that they weren't at risk.

18:32.060 --> 18:33.493
But ACN loved it,
didn't they?

18:35.540 --> 18:37.098
Now, can you
honestly say

18:37.150 --> 18:38.629
you were thinking
of the community
when you did that?

18:38.680 --> 18:40.716
I'm always thinking
of the community.

18:40.770 --> 18:42.544
In fact,
my work just secured

18:42.590 --> 18:44.467
a block grant program
for the Lower 9th.

18:44.510 --> 18:47.240
Oh, I guess
_ it's a little easier
just to put a hand out

18:47.300 --> 18:49.427
than it is to get it dirty
doing the hard work.

18:49.470 --> 18:52.257
You know, you sound
like a broken record.

18:52.300 --> 18:54.905
In 30 years, you'll be
at the same parties,

18:54.950 --> 18:56.690
spouting the same
party language

18:56.740 --> 19:00.255
and using day-old methods
for what has become a new day.

19:00.310 --> 19:04.872
Mother Brown always said
that change requires
that we change, too.

19:04.920 --> 19:07.138
I see that now.
Thank you.

19:07.180 --> 19:09.796
Nova, you can name-drop
as much as you want to,
but know that working for her

19:09.840 --> 19:12.400
still means_
that you're Sitting
at a table somewhere.

19:12.450 --> 19:15.055
And you're making decisions
that affect the rest of us.

19:15.110 --> 19:17.237
You can be in the community,
or you can be in a boardroom,

19:17.280 --> 19:18.884
but you can't be
in two places at once.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.192
Jasmine:
Yo, this a party.
Stop trying to pick a fight.

