23:50.080 --> 23:52.719
Woman:
Yeah, just put it
in the washer.

23:54.250 --> 23:55.649
Can you stop
distracting me

23:55.690 --> 23:59.069
with all your sighing
and fidgeting?

23:59.130 --> 24:01.212
Don't you have
something to study for?

24:01.260 --> 24:02.693
I'm trying.

24:04.090 --> 24:06.433
What's the matter?

24:06.480 --> 24:08.038
It's that display.

24:08.090 --> 24:09.819
How did I not
even notice it before?

24:09.880 --> 24:14.829
Like, the general--
his face is haunting me.

24:16.540 --> 24:18.701
Well, what are you
gonna do about it?

24:18.760 --> 24:20.796
I know you watch
the news.

24:20.850 --> 24:24.320
And all these
old Dixie statues being
torn down left and right?

24:24.370 --> 24:25.974
They didn't get
torn down by themselves.

24:26.020 --> 24:28.238
People did that.

24:28.290 --> 24:29.769
People who were haunted
by them did that.

24:29.810 --> 24:33.246
Yeah, right,
but those were
public property, okay?

24:33.290 --> 24:36.111
The city had to listen
to a lot of complaints
before they took it down.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.331
So Gardini doesn't _have
to listen to complaints?

24:38.380 --> 24:41.861
No, I'm just saying, babe,
like, it's a private school.

24:41.910 --> 24:45.084
You know what I mean?
They have a lot more room
to do what they wanna do.

24:45.130 --> 24:46.472
Or what their donors
want them to do.

24:46.520 --> 24:49.569
Money doesn't always
get you a pass.

24:49.610 --> 24:51.919
Make some noise.

24:51.960 --> 24:53.916
Never know
what'll come of it.

24:56.050 --> 24:59.315
And it's cut down
our processmg time
by 100/0,

24:59.360 --> 25:03.273
so you get to market faster
with higher sucrose content.

25:04.800 --> 25:07.189
That is an A-plus
sales pitch.

25:07.240 --> 25:09.367
_ You were a star
in busmess school,
weren't you?

25:09.420 --> 25:11.456
[ both chuckle ]

25:11.510 --> 25:13.933
As a matter of fact,
I was.

25:13.990 --> 25:15.935
I was not.

25:15.990 --> 25:19.289
Basically spent
the two years traveling
on Columbia's dime.

25:19.340 --> 25:24.812
Went to Morocco, Norway,
hiked the Inca Trail in Peru.

25:24.870 --> 25:27.862
I went to Argentina,

25:27.910 --> 25:29.901
but I also studied.

25:29.960 --> 25:31.348
[ chuckles ]

25:35.140 --> 25:37.529
You free for dinner
tonight?

25:37.570 --> 25:40.926
To discuss the terms
of your contract?

25:40.970 --> 25:43.097
To get to know
each other better.

25:43.150 --> 25:44.014
A date.

25:45.970 --> 25:48.018
[ chuckles ]

25:48.060 --> 25:53.157
That's, um--
that's very kind,

25:53.200 --> 25:55.714
but I'm seeing someone.

25:55.770 --> 25:56.714
Is it serious?

25:59.550 --> 26:02.075
Yeah.

26:02.120 --> 26:04.031
So soon after
your divorce?

26:06.430 --> 26:08.250
I'm not being
judgmental.

26:08.300 --> 26:10.473
I'm only speaking
from experience.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.913
And if the only way to get you
to agree to dinner with me

26:17.960 --> 26:21.839
is to say
we'll discuss business,
then we'll discuss business.

26:21.880 --> 26:25.008
- [ bell ringing ]
- [ chatter ]

26:40.770 --> 26:43.853
Darlene:
Has he asked
for Ralph Angel yet?

26:43.900 --> 26:45.765
Darla:
I changed the subject.

26:49.250 --> 26:51.639
Well, you're going to have
to tell him something soon.

26:51.690 --> 26:54.124
No. I don't have
to tell him anything.

26:54.170 --> 26:55.603
Not now.

26:57.870 --> 27:00.088
[ sighs ]

27:05.530 --> 27:07.316
What if he doesn't
come back?

27:09.580 --> 27:11.571
What if he gives up on me?

27:11.630 --> 27:14.406
I sense goodness
in Ralph Angel.

27:14.450 --> 27:16.975
- He won't.
- How do you know that?

27:17.020 --> 27:19.454
Darla, you are blessed.

27:19.500 --> 27:21.195
[ scoffs ]

27:21.240 --> 27:22.889
I don't feel
very blessed right now.

27:22.940 --> 27:25.113
Blessed doesn't mean
your life is cherries.

27:25.160 --> 27:29.984
It means
even when it isn't,
you keep at it.

27:30.030 --> 27:35.388
Even after
you mess up bad,

27:35.430 --> 27:38.160
people still want
to see you be okay.

27:44.010 --> 27:47.696
Nine times...

27:47.750 --> 27:52.050
your father and I
came down here
looking for you

27:52.100 --> 27:54.409
after you
stopped calling.

27:54.450 --> 27:57.362
I searched
homeless shelters,

27:57.410 --> 28:00.709
rehabs,
halfway houses.

28:00.760 --> 28:04.196
I saw and imagined
too much.

28:09.030 --> 28:11.498
I started drinking again.

28:11.550 --> 28:12.949
What?

28:16.300 --> 28:19.201
23 years sober.

28:23.130 --> 28:26.179
Until I came down here.

28:26.220 --> 28:29.781
- Mom.
- You were too young
to remember.

28:29.830 --> 28:31.707
And I didn't
want you to know.

28:35.140 --> 28:37.836
With the social circles
your father runs in...

28:37.890 --> 28:40.279
He's a proud man, Darla.

28:40.320 --> 28:42.709
It's not the type
of thing to talk about.

28:45.150 --> 28:46.754
I'm glad we're here.

28:48.590 --> 28:52.629
I'm glad I'm here,
I'm glad you're here.

28:52.680 --> 28:56.719
We're blessed because
we love each other

28:56.770 --> 29:00.467
and it is that
"no matter what"
kind of love.

29:00.520 --> 29:02.943
And Blue is blessed
because of Ralph Angel.

29:03.000 --> 29:04.649
It's the same kind
of love.

29:04.690 --> 29:06.863
I can see it
in his eyes.

29:06.910 --> 29:08.821
He just needs time.

29:12.570 --> 29:15.095
[ swing creaking ]

29:23.840 --> 29:25.102
Anchorman: _
Declared a public nUIsance

29:25.150 --> 29:26.845
by the New Orleans
City Council,

29:26.890 --> 29:29.450
four Confederate monuments
Will come down.

29:29.500 --> 29:33.379
- This one is the last...
- It's the Lee Circle
from earlier this year.

29:33.420 --> 29:36.059
Oh. Right.

29:36.120 --> 29:39.988
The Confederate monuments
coming down.

29:40.030 --> 29:43.329
I've been
so busy with harvest,
I haven't really kept track

29:43.390 --> 29:45.381
of all the twists
and turns of that.

29:45.430 --> 29:46.601
[ newscast continues ]

29:50.170 --> 29:51.990
- [ video stops ]
- I know it's important,

29:52.050 --> 29:54.564
what's going on
in New Orleans.

29:54.610 --> 29:58.000
Can't live here
and not know that.

29:59.710 --> 30:01.439
But life goes on.

30:03.140 --> 30:06.496
Yeah, I remember
when I used to think that.

30:06.540 --> 30:07.791
The way I see it...

30:10.020 --> 30:15.026
to give into that
is to live in bondage,

30:15.070 --> 30:16.458
to fear.

30:16.510 --> 30:18.546
It seems like
when you're black,

30:18.590 --> 30:20.808
living in fear
is just good common sense.

30:20.860 --> 30:22.157
Okay.

30:24.030 --> 30:25.725
What is all this?

30:27.080 --> 30:27.944
[ laptop closes ]

30:31.260 --> 30:36.471
Gardini Prep
has the sword

30:36.530 --> 30:39.567
of a Confederate general
on display.

30:41.310 --> 30:44.188
And every day,
people walk by it
like it's nothing.

30:46.060 --> 30:47.834
You know,
like it's okay.

30:49.630 --> 30:53.919
Like, they'll look at it
and they see history.

30:53.980 --> 30:55.493
What do you see?

30:56.980 --> 31:01.064
Well, at first
I didn't see,
but I...

31:01.120 --> 31:04.112
And now that I do,
I see blood.

31:04.160 --> 31:06.287
Why do they have the nerve
to put it on display

31:06.340 --> 31:09.036
like murder is something
to be proud of?

31:09.080 --> 31:10.559
You know,
it's the same thing

31:10.600 --> 31:14.900
with, like,
that stupid flag
with the "X" on it.

31:14.960 --> 31:17.258
When I look at that,
I see a bull's-eye, Mom,

31:17.310 --> 31:22.009
on-- on me, on--
on Uncle Rah, on Dad.

31:22.050 --> 31:24.780
Man, sometimes
I just hate being here.

31:24.830 --> 31:28.527
Like,
I hate being here.

31:28.580 --> 31:31.447
I see why people leave
the first chance they get.

31:31.490 --> 31:33.663
Well, that's not
totally fair.

31:33.710 --> 31:35.268
I came back.

31:39.760 --> 31:41.102
But you're right.

31:43.030 --> 31:45.419
Pain is here.

31:45.460 --> 31:46.540
Definitely.

31:46.600 --> 31:48.465
And hate.

31:51.730 --> 31:54.517
But there's also triumph

31:54.560 --> 31:57.905
and community.

31:59.560 --> 32:01.209
And love.

32:01.260 --> 32:04.218
All right,
you're starting to sound
a little soft, Mom.

32:06.570 --> 32:11.189
Maybe,
but whatever is here,
whatever it is...

32:13.840 --> 32:15.398
it's real.

32:15.450 --> 32:20.228
And I think I wanna
take a chance on it.

32:24.020 --> 32:26.068
Are you talking
about Remy?

32:31.640 --> 32:34.074
He's helped me
in so many ways.

32:34.120 --> 32:39.035
Learning about
the sugarcane business
and the community.

32:39.080 --> 32:41.036
[ sighs ]
We've gotten close,
you know?

32:41.080 --> 32:45.699
And, to my surprise,
he makes me laugh.

32:47.310 --> 32:49.130
Are you in love
with him?

32:52.970 --> 32:54.915
I'm trying
to figure that out.

32:58.450 --> 33:01.578
The other day, he--

33:01.630 --> 33:05.009
he asked me
about having kids.

33:05.070 --> 33:06.014
Kids?

33:06.070 --> 33:07.628
[ scoffs ]
Really?

33:07.680 --> 33:09.898
Mm-hmm.

33:09.940 --> 33:11.328
- You're kidding.
- It's weird, right?

33:14.200 --> 33:15.599
I don't know.

33:18.080 --> 33:19.559
I mean, that's cool,
I guess.

33:24.300 --> 33:26.256
Remy's a cool guy.

33:29.920 --> 33:30.818
I like him.

33:32.090 --> 33:35.093
That means a lot
to me.

33:35.140 --> 33:36.437
More than you know.

33:41.800 --> 33:43.574
So, uh...

33:43.630 --> 33:46.622
I guess that means
I'll be somebody's
big brother soon.

33:46.670 --> 33:49.059
- Mm-mmm.
Way too soon.
-[laughs]

33:49.110 --> 33:51.146
- [ rain pattering ]
' [ Playing ]

33:54.240 --> 33:56.856
[ sighs ]

