- Blue finally
fell asleep.
- Oh...

34:04.780 --> 34:07.294
[ playing piano ]

34:10.480 --> 34:11.697
You remember.

34:11.740 --> 34:13.822
- Just the chorus.
- Aw.

34:13.870 --> 34:16.179
That was
my favorite part.

34:16.220 --> 34:19.041
[ both playing piano ]

34:27.060 --> 34:28.049
[ playing stops ]

34:28.100 --> 34:29.749
[ chuckles ]

34:29.800 --> 34:32.667
It's about time for Blue
to start lessons, huh?

34:36.630 --> 34:38.632
[ sighs ]

34:44.160 --> 34:47.379
Ralph Angel has a lot
to think about, honey.

34:51.780 --> 34:54.385
He needs some space.

34:54.440 --> 34:56.692
And maybe you do, too.

34:56.740 --> 34:58.731
I don't wanna
give him space.

35:01.220 --> 35:02.869
I just want him.

35:05.360 --> 35:07.225
[ groans ]

35:16.110 --> 35:18.453
I shouldn't
have ever gone home.

35:18.500 --> 35:22.413
_ It was
just supposed to be
one last weekend

35:22.460 --> 35:25.111
with my old crew
from high school.

35:25.160 --> 35:27.333
Just one night.

35:30.650 --> 35:32.686
And it got
out of control.

35:34.480 --> 35:37.085
I got out of control.

35:39.570 --> 35:42.789
It wasn't even clear to me
what was happening

35:42.830 --> 35:46.789
until it was all just...

35:46.840 --> 35:48.228
happening.

35:55.800 --> 35:57.711
Was there more than
one guy?

36:01.590 --> 36:02.978
I don't know.

36:05.160 --> 36:06.639
I really don't.

36:08.250 --> 36:09.547
I wasn't myself then.

36:14.690 --> 36:16.339
I've been there--

36:16.390 --> 36:18.858
standing outside
of yourself,

36:18.910 --> 36:20.992
doing things
you'd never do,

36:21.040 --> 36:24.430
without an assist
from your demons.

36:24.480 --> 36:27.608
And we all have them.

36:27.660 --> 36:31.096
Some of us
just do a better job
of controlling them.

36:33.360 --> 36:37.273
You can come home, sweetheart.
You need to know that.

36:37.320 --> 36:40.141
Your father and I
can support you and Blue.

36:50.990 --> 36:52.639
Thank you, Mom.

36:54.120 --> 36:55.769
Thank you
for forgiving me.

36:57.470 --> 37:00.200
But... I can't
take Blue away

37:00.260 --> 37:01.773
from the only family
he's ever known.

37:01.820 --> 37:04.163
We're his family, too.

37:04.220 --> 37:06.780
He should get
to know us as well.

37:06.830 --> 37:10.789
It would give Ralph Angel
the time and space he needs.

37:10.830 --> 37:13.651
And you could have
a fresh start.

37:13.700 --> 37:16.442
You deserve one.

37:16.490 --> 37:19.835
Come back to this route
and take your heart
to higher self...

37:19.880 --> 37:21.495
- Hollywood: Come on.
- What the...?

37:21.540 --> 37:22.700
Hold it down.

37:24.500 --> 37:25.922
Oh!

37:25.980 --> 37:28.494
Oh... Ralph Angel,
what's going on?

37:28.550 --> 37:30.541
He was at True's boat
with this.

37:30.590 --> 37:32.808
A whole bunch more
out there, too.

37:32.850 --> 37:34.590
What's wrong
with you, baby?

37:44.040 --> 37:46.076
- Charley: Come on in!
- [ music playing on radio ]

37:48.440 --> 37:50.169
Hey!

37:51.660 --> 37:54.823
- Someone likes you.
- Oh. [ chuckles ]

37:54.880 --> 37:56.302
It's from Martin.

37:56.360 --> 37:57.566
A "thank you."

38:00.140 --> 38:02.096
Really?

38:02.140 --> 38:03.539
Just a "thank you,"
huh?

38:05.500 --> 38:09.402
He came by for a meeting,
asked for a drink.

38:09.460 --> 38:12.020
Coffee was
the strongest thing I had.

38:12.070 --> 38:14.675
So...
[ chuckles ]

38:14.720 --> 38:17.109
It's-- it's just
a joke between us.

38:17.160 --> 38:18.718
18-year?

38:20.640 --> 38:23.723
That's a pretty
expensive joke.

38:23.770 --> 38:25.169
Remy Newell...

38:27.520 --> 38:29.078
I believe...

38:32.520 --> 38:33.737
you're jealous,
aren't you?

38:38.350 --> 38:42.616
Farmers have been cancelling
on me left and right.

38:42.660 --> 38:44.616
Bennington is...

38:46.190 --> 38:47.612
a necessary evil.

38:47.670 --> 38:49.490
Business.

38:49.540 --> 38:51.929
- He's a Landry.
- And I'm handling my business.

38:51.980 --> 38:53.936
Hmm.
Does he know that?

38:55.940 --> 38:58.363
I think you're making
too much of this.

38:58.420 --> 38:59.717
Maybe.

39:02.120 --> 39:05.760
But that mind of yours,
it-- it's actually
one of the things

39:05.820 --> 39:07.947
that I admire most
about you.

39:07.990 --> 39:11.039
'Cause you're always
thinking five steps ahead.

39:11.080 --> 39:14.254
And you're also willing
to do the unexpected.

39:16.520 --> 39:18.340
It's how you're built.

39:19.660 --> 39:20.524
Thank you.

39:22.440 --> 39:25.227
- I think.
- Look, I'm just
reminding you--

39:25.270 --> 39:28.182
whatever game
you're playing,

39:28.230 --> 39:30.448
don't put
all your chips
on the table.

39:33.240 --> 39:36.755
I know how to deal
with men like Bennington.

39:46.470 --> 39:49.030
[ door rattling ]

39:50.950 --> 39:53.942
Hey, hey

39:54.000 --> 39:55.809
Oh

39:57.610 --> 40:00.477
Hey, hey, hey

40:00.520 --> 40:04.399
When your heart
is a stranger

40:04.440 --> 40:08.137
And you know
you didn't treat it right

40:08.180 --> 40:11.183
When your love
is in danger...

40:11.230 --> 40:15.269
- God, hear me.
- And you know you're
gonna need to fight...

40:17.110 --> 40:18.793
Hear me real clear.

40:22.070 --> 40:23.753
Hear me real good.

40:23.810 --> 40:27.541
When you can't learn

40:27.590 --> 40:30.809
When you
can't learn...

40:30.860 --> 40:32.760
Violet:
Whatever this is...

40:34.250 --> 40:35.774
take it back.

40:38.210 --> 40:40.599
Take it all back.

40:40.650 --> 40:43.904
I've given enough...

40:43.960 --> 40:45.689
Violet:
Please, God, please.

40:45.740 --> 40:48.527
Now you're just
rolling the dice...

